---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
import GitHubIcon from "../components/icons/GitHubIcon.astro";
---

<Base
  title="Home"
  description="skill7 is the front door for hosted agent tools and the heurema plugin marketplace. Open Sift in the browser or browse the marketplace separately."
>
  <section class="relative overflow-hidden py-24 sm:py-28">
    <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-dots opacity-60 pointer-events-none" />
    <div
      class="absolute top-0 right-0 h-80 w-80 rounded-full blur-3xl pointer-events-none"
      style="background: radial-gradient(circle, rgba(0,229,160,0.10) 0%, transparent 70%);"
    />
    <div
      class="absolute bottom-0 left-0 h-96 w-96 rounded-full blur-3xl pointer-events-none"
      style="background: radial-gradient(circle, rgba(0,180,216,0.08) 0%, transparent 70%);"
    />

    <div class="relative mx-auto max-w-6xl">
      <div class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 rounded-full border border-acid/40 bg-acid-muted px-3 py-1">
        <span class="h-1.5 w-1.5 rounded-full bg-acid animate-pulse"></span>
        <span class="text-xs font-mono font-medium text-acid">Hosted products + plugin marketplace</span>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-8 grid gap-12 lg:grid-cols-[1.2fr_0.8fr] lg:items-end">
        <div>
          <h1 class="font-heading text-5xl font-bold tracking-tight sm:text-6xl">
            <span class="text-gradient-hero">skill7</span>
            <br />
            <span class="text-dark-hi">for products, not just plugins</span>
          </h1>
          <p class="mt-8 max-w-2xl text-lg leading-relaxed text-dark-lo">
            Use <span class="text-dark-hi font-medium">Sift</span> as a browser product with account-based access,
            or browse the <span class="text-dark-hi font-medium">Marketplace</span> for installable heurema plugins.
            The public site is now split on purpose: hosted apps live on their own pages, and plugin install docs stay friction-free.
          </p>

          <div class="mt-10 flex flex-col gap-3 sm:flex-row">
            <a href="/sift" class="btn-primary justify-center sm:w-auto">
              Open Sift
            </a>
            <a href="/marketplace" class="btn-secondary justify-center sm:w-auto">
              Browse Marketplace
            </a>
            <a href="/auth/login?return_to=%2Fsift%2Fapp" class="btn-ghost justify-center sm:w-auto">
              Create account / sign in
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="grid gap-4">
          <div class="card border-gradient-acid">
            <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-3">
              <div>
                <p class="text-xs font-mono font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest text-acid">Hosted product</p>
                <h2 class="mt-2 font-heading text-2xl font-bold text-dark-hi">Sift</h2>
              </div>
              <span class="badge bg-acid-muted text-acid border-acid/40">new flow</span>
            </div>
            <p class="mt-4 text-sm leading-relaxed text-dark-lo">
              Browser access, account entry, and a dedicated product page. No more hiding Sift inside plugin marketplace copy.
            </p>
            <ul class="mt-5 space-y-2 text-sm text-dark-lo">
              <li>Hosted news intelligence for agents</li>
              <li>Session-based browser access</li>
              <li>Separate product navigation and onboarding</li>
            </ul>
            <a href="/sift" class="btn-primary mt-6 w-full justify-center">Go to Sift</a>
          </div>

          <div class="card">
            <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-3">
              <div>
                <p class="text-xs font-mono font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest text-cyan">Registry</p>
                <h2 class="mt-2 font-heading text-2xl font-bold text-dark-hi">Marketplace</h2>
              </div>
              <GitHubIcon />
            </div>
            <p class="mt-4 text-sm leading-relaxed text-dark-lo">
              Same plugin catalog, same CLI install flow, but clearly separated from hosted product UX.
            </p>
            <div class="mt-5 rounded-xl border border-dark-line bg-dark-code px-4 py-3 font-mono text-sm text-dark-hi">
              <span class="text-acid">$</span> claude plugin marketplace add heurema/emporium
            </div>
            <a href="/marketplace" class="btn-secondary mt-6 w-full justify-center">Open Marketplace</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="border-t border-dark-line py-16">
    <div class="mx-auto grid max-w-6xl gap-6 lg:grid-cols-3">
      <div class="card-sm">
        <p class="text-xs font-mono uppercase tracking-widest text-acid">1</p>
        <h2 class="mt-3 font-heading text-2xl font-semibold text-dark-hi">Pick the right mode</h2>
        <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-relaxed text-dark-lo">
          Use <a href="/sift" class="text-acid hover:text-acid-glow transition-colors">Sift</a> for hosted product access,
          or <a href="/marketplace" class="text-acid hover:text-acid-glow transition-colors">Marketplace</a> for local plugin installs.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="card-sm">
        <p class="text-xs font-mono uppercase tracking-widest text-acid">2</p>
        <h2 class="mt-3 font-heading text-2xl font-semibold text-dark-hi">Authenticate only where it matters</h2>
        <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-relaxed text-dark-lo">
          Marketplace pages stay public. Account entry appears only on the hosted Sift path, so the plugin catalog keeps its zero-friction install flow.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="card-sm">
        <p class="text-xs font-mono uppercase tracking-widest text-acid">3</p>
        <h2 class="mt-3 font-heading text-2xl font-semibold text-dark-hi">Grow without mixing models</h2>
        <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-relaxed text-dark-lo">
          Products can get their own landing pages and auth flows. Plugins stay installable docs. That split scales much better than making everything look like `emporium`.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
